AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1694 House Bill No. 1477*
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 56, Chapter 1, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
56-1-111.
(a)
(1) The general assembly finds that:
(A) Insurance claims handling directly affects the health, safety,
and financial security of residents of this state, particularly elderly and
vulnerable populations;
(B) Transparency in regulatory enforcement promotes
accountability and public trust;
(C) Certain confidentiality provisions currently prevent the public
from knowing whether insurers repeatedly fail to timely adjust, investigate,
or pay valid claims; and
(D) Disclosure of substantiated claims-handling violations, when
properly redacted, does not require disclosure of trade secrets or
personally identifying information.
(2) It is the intent of the general assembly to increase transparency
regarding insurer claims practices that affect the public, while maintaining
appropriate protections for personal data and proprietary business information.
